item.title: OpenVINO, Optimum-Intel, CPU: An Exploration in Model Optimization
item.description: OpenVINO represents an open-source toolkit designed for the optimization and deployment of deep learning models. Acting as the interface between the Transformers and Diffusers libraries, Optimum-Intel seamlessly integrates with various Intel tools and libraries, facilitating the acceleration of end-to-end pipelines on Intel architectures. This post documents my journey as I set up and execute example code on my aging laptop, exploring the application of Quantization-aware Training (QAT) and the Token Merging method to optimize the UNet model within the Stable Diffusion pipeline.
